27/* \summary: Marvell Extended Distributed Switch Architecture (MEDSA) printer */
28
29#ifdef HAVE_CONFIG_H
30#include "config.h"
31#endif
32
33#include <netdissect-stdinc.h>
34
35#include "netdissect.h"
36#include "ether.h"
37#include "ethertype.h"
38#include "addrtoname.h"
39#include "extract.h"
40
41static const char tstr[] = "[|MEDSA]";
42
43/*
44 * Marvell Extended Distributed Switch Archiecture.
45 *
46 * A Marvell propriatary header used for passing packets to/from
47 * specific ports of a switch. There is no open specification of this
48 * header, but is documented in the Marvell Switch data sheets. For
49 * background, see:
50 *
51 * https://lwn.net/Articles/302333/
52 */
53struct medsa_pkthdr {
54 u_char bytes[6];
55 u_short ether_type;
56};
57
58/* Bytes 0 and 1 are reserved and should contain 0 */
59#define TAG(medsa) (medsa->bytes[2] >> 6)
60#define TAG_TO_CPU 0
61#define TAG_FROM_CPU 1
62#define TAG_FORWARD 3
63#define SRC_TAG(medsa) ((medsa->bytes[2] >> 5) & 0x01)
64#define SRC_DEV(medsa) (medsa->bytes[2] & 0x1f)
65#define SRC_PORT(medsa) ((medsa->bytes[3] >> 3) & 0x01f)
66#define TRUNK(medsa) ((medsa->bytes[3] >> 2) & 0x01)
67#define CODE(medsa) ((medsa->bytes[3] & 0x06) | \
68 ((medsa->bytes[4] >> 4) & 0x01))
69#define CODE_BDPU 0
70#define CODE_IGMP_MLD 2
71#define CODE_ARP_MIRROR 4
72#define CFI(medsa) (medsa->bytes[3] & 0x01)
73#define PRI(medsa) (medsa->bytes[4] >> 5)
74#define VID(medsa) (((u_short)(medsa->bytes[4] & 0xf) << 8 | \
75 medsa->bytes[5]))
76
77static const struct tok tag_values[] = {
78 { TAG_TO_CPU, "To_CPU" },
79 { TAG_FROM_CPU, "From_CPU" },
80 { TAG_FORWARD, "Forward" },
81 { 0, NULL },
82};
83
84static const struct tok code_values[] = {
85 { CODE_BDPU, "BDPU" },
86 { CODE_IGMP_MLD, "IGMP/MLD" },
87 { CODE_ARP_MIRROR, "APR_Mirror" },
88 { 0, NULL },
89};
90
91static void
92medsa_print_full(netdissect_options *ndo,
93 const struct medsa_pkthdr *medsa,
94 u_int caplen)
95{
96 u_char tag = TAG(medsa);
97
98 ND_PRINT((ndo, "%s",
99 tok2str(tag_values, "Unknown (%u)", tag)));
100
101 switch (tag) {
102 case TAG_TO_CPU:
103 ND_PRINT((ndo, ", %stagged", SRC_TAG(medsa) ? "" : "un"));
104 ND_PRINT((ndo, ", dev.port:vlan %d.%d:%d",
105 SRC_DEV(medsa), SRC_PORT(medsa), VID(medsa)));
106
107 ND_PRINT((ndo, ", %s",
108 tok2str(code_values, "Unknown (%u)", CODE(medsa))));
109 if (CFI(medsa))
110 ND_PRINT((ndo, ", CFI"));
111
112 ND_PRINT((ndo, ", pri %d: ", PRI(medsa)));
113 break;
114 case TAG_FROM_CPU:
115 ND_PRINT((ndo, ", %stagged", SRC_TAG(medsa) ? "" : "un"));
116 ND_PRINT((ndo, ", dev.port:vlan %d.%d:%d",
117 SRC_DEV(medsa), SRC_PORT(medsa), VID(medsa)));
118
119 if (CFI(medsa))
120 ND_PRINT((ndo, ", CFI"));
121
122 ND_PRINT((ndo, ", pri %d: ", PRI(medsa)));
123 break;
124 case TAG_FORWARD:
125 ND_PRINT((ndo, ", %stagged", SRC_TAG(medsa) ? "" : "un"));
126 if (TRUNK(medsa))
127 ND_PRINT((ndo, ", dev.trunk:vlan %d.%d:%d",
128 SRC_DEV(medsa), SRC_PORT(medsa), VID(medsa)));
129 else
130 ND_PRINT((ndo, ", dev.port:vlan %d.%d:%d",
131 SRC_DEV(medsa), SRC_PORT(medsa), VID(medsa)));
132
133 if (CFI(medsa))
134 ND_PRINT((ndo, ", CFI"));
135
136 ND_PRINT((ndo, ", pri %d: ", PRI(medsa)));
137 break;
138 default:
139 ND_DEFAULTPRINT((const u_char *)medsa, caplen);
140 return;
141 }
142}
143
144void
145medsa_print(netdissect_options *ndo,
146 const u_char *bp, u_int length, u_int caplen,
147 const struct lladdr_info *src, const struct lladdr_info *dst)
148{
149 const struct medsa_pkthdr *medsa;
150 u_short ether_type;
151
152 medsa = (const struct medsa_pkthdr *)bp;
153 ND_TCHECK(*medsa);
154
155 if (!ndo->ndo_eflag)
156 ND_PRINT((ndo, "MEDSA %d.%d:%d: ",
157 SRC_DEV(medsa), SRC_PORT(medsa), VID(medsa)));
158 else
159 medsa_print_full(ndo, medsa, caplen);
160
161 bp += 8;
162 length -= 8;
163 caplen -= 8;
164
165 ether_type = EXTRACT_16BITS(&medsa->ether_type);
166 if (ether_type <= ETHERMTU) {
167 /* Try to print the LLC-layer header & higher layers */
168 if (llc_print(ndo, bp, length, caplen, src, dst) < 0) {
169 /* packet type not known, print raw packet */
170 if (!ndo->ndo_suppress_default_print)
171 ND_DEFAULTPRINT(bp, caplen);
172 }
173 } else {
174 if (ndo->ndo_eflag)
175 ND_PRINT((ndo, "ethertype %s (0x%04x) ",
176 tok2str(ethertype_values, "Unknown",
177 ether_type),
178 ether_type));
179 if (ethertype_print(ndo, ether_type, bp, length, caplen, src, dst) == 0) {
180 /* ether_type not known, print raw packet */
181 if (!ndo->ndo_eflag)
182 ND_PRINT((ndo, "ethertype %s (0x%04x) ",
183 tok2str(ethertype_values, "Unknown",
184 ether_type),
185 ether_type));
186
187 if (!ndo->ndo_suppress_default_print)
188 ND_DEFAULTPRINT(bp, caplen);
189 }
190 }
191 return;
192trunc:
193 ND_PRINT((ndo, "%s", tstr));
194}
